          </dl>
        </dd>

        
                  <dt>Publication History</dt>
          <dd>
                                        <p>
                                              Arthur Pope, "The New Fogg Art Museum--The Collection of Drawings", <em>The Arts</em> (July 1927), vol. XII, no. 1, pp. 25-28, ill. p. 27
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Arthur E. Popham, "Notes on Drawings: ? Andrea Mantegna", <em>Old Master Drawings</em> (March 1932), vol. VI, no. 24, p. 62, p. 62; repr. pl. 58, n.p.
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Agnes Mongan and Paul J. Sachs, <em>Drawings in the Fogg Museum of Art</em>, Harvard University Press (Cambridge, 1940), vol. 1, cat. no. 24, pp. 18-19; vol. 2, repr. fig. 25
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Ruth Wedgwood Kennedy, <em>Italian Drawings, 1330-1780</em>, exh. cat., Smith College Museum of Art (Northampton, MA, 1941), cat. no. 45, n.p.
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Bryan Holme, ed., <em>Master Drawings</em>, The Studio Publications Incorporated (New York, NY and London, England, 1943), pl. 12
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Jean Cassou, "Ingres, Cezanne, Le Fresnaye, Picasso: On the Demarche of the Creative Thought", <em>Gazette des Beaux-Arts</em> (April 1948), VI series, vol. XXXVI, pp. 239-250, repr. fig. 4, p. 242
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              <em>Diamond Jubilee Exhibition: Masterpieces of Drawing</em>, exh. cat., Philadelphia Museum of Art (Philadelphia, PA, 1950), repr. no. 13, n.p.
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              John Coolidge, ed., <em>Picture Book: Survey of the Fogg Collections</em>, Fogg Art Museum (Cambridge, 1951), vol. 1, cat. no. 9, n.p.
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Erika Tietze-Conrat, <em>Mantegna: Paintings, Drawings, Engravings</em>, Phaidon (London, England, 1955), pp. 203 and 205
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Helen Gardner, <em>Art Through the Ages</em>, ed. Sumner McK. Crosby, Harcourt, Brace and Co. (New York, NY, 1959), p. 13, repr. fig. 0-12
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Giovanni Paccagnini and Amalia Mezzetti, <em>Andrea Mantegna</em>, exh. cat., Neri Pozza Editore (Venice, Italy, 1961), under cat. no. 121, p. 164, as Mantegna
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Winslow Ames, <em>Great Drawings of All Time [vol. 1: Italian]</em>, ed. Ira Moskowitz, Shorewood Publishers Inc. (New York, 1962), cat. no. 69, n.p., repr. color
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Agnes Mongan, <em>Memorial Exhibition: Works of Art from the Collection of Paul J. Sachs [1878-1965]: given and bequeathed to the Fogg Art Museum, Harvard University, Cambridge, Massachusetts</em>, exh. cat., Harvard University (Cambridge, MA, 1965), cat. no. 4, n.p., repr.
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Maria Bellonci and Niny Garavaglia, <em>L'opera completa del Mantegna</em>, Rizzoli (Milan, 1967), under cat. no. 34A, p. 97; repr. same page
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Konrad Oberhuber, <em>European Master Drawings of Six Centuries from the Collection of the Fogg Art Museum</em>, exh. cat., National Museum of Western Art (Tokyo, 1979), cat. no. 1, n.p., pl. 1, repr. (detail used as cover)
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Beverly Louise Brown, <em>Prints and Drawings of the Quattrocento</em>, exh. cat., Fogg Art Museum (Cambridge, MA, 1981), p. 7; cat. no. 17, p. 19
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Kristin A. Mortimer and William G. Klingelhofer, <em>Harvard University Art Museums: A Guide to the Collections</em>, Harvard University Art Museums and Abbeville Press (Cambridge and New York, 1986), cat. no. 247, pp. 214-215, repr. color
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Ronald Lightbown, <em>Mantegna: With a Complete Catalogue of the Paintings, Drawings, and Prints</em>, University of California Press (Berkeley, CA, 1986), repr. pl. 213, n.p.; under cat. no 16, p. 413; cat. no. 182, p. 483
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Agnes Mongan, Konrad Oberhuber, and Jonathan Bober, <em>The Famous Italian Drawings at the Fogg Art Museum in Cambridge</em>, Silvana Editoriale (Milan, Italy, 1988), cat. no. 7, n.p., and pp. 10, 18, and 24, repr. color, and under cat. no. 41...
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Suzanne Boorsch and Keith Christiansen, <em>Andrea Mantegna</em>, exh. cat., ed. Jane Martineau, Royal Academy of Arts / Metropolitan Museum of Art (Milan, Italy, 1992), cat. no. 20, pp. 167-168 and p. 405, repr. color pl. 20, as after Mantegna
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Robert Munman, "Two Drawings by Andrea Mantegna: A Simili/Modelli Problem Reconsidered", <em>Momus: rivista di studi umanisitici</em> (1996), vol. V-VI, pp. 5-25, pp. 5-25, repr. p. 6, fig. 1, as Andrea Mantegna
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Michael Wiemers, <em>Bildform und Werkgenese: Studien zur zeichnerischen Bildvorbereitung in der italienischen Malerei zwischen 1450 und 1490</em>, Deutscher Kunstverlag (Munich, Germany, 1996), pp. 173, 175-76, repr. p. 176, fig. 158, as Mantegna
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Penley Knipe, "Grounds on Paper: An Examination of Eight Early Drawings" (thesis (certificate in conservation), Straus Center for Conservation and Technical Studies, 1998), Unpublished, pp. 1-22 passim
                             </p>
